'''''Factomania''''' is a factual television series that is set to first broadcast on [[BBC Knowledge (international)|BBC Knowledge]] and [[BBC HD (international)|BBC HD]] in 2014. The hosts for the ten-part series are [[Greg Foot]], Fran Scott and [[Dominic Byrne]].<ref name="BBC">{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/worldwide/160513coolstuff.html | title=BBC Worldwide announces <U+2018>Really Cool Stuff<U+2019> (working title) - the latest original commission for its international channel portfolio | work=BBC Worldwide | date=16 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.onscreenasia.com/article/bbc-worldwide-announces-really-cool-stuff/12322 | title=BBC Worldwide announces <U+201C>Really Cool Stuff<U+201D> | work=OnScreen Asia | date=20 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Mirrah, Nur}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/news/commissioning/bbcw-orders-pop-science-series/5056171.article | title=BBCW orders pop science series | work=Broadcast Now | date=16 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=White, Peter}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://realscreen.com/2013/05/16/bbc-worldwide-commissions-really-cool-stuff/ | title=BBC Worldwide commissions <U+201C>Really Cool Stuff<U+201D> | work=RealScreen | date=16 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Ritchie, Kevin}}</ref>

==Production==
Factomania is a 360 Production for [[BBC Worldwide]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/worldwide/100214showcase.html | title=BBC Worldwide welcomes a fantastic line up of TV talent to its biggest and best Showcase ever | work=BBC Worldwide | date=10 February 2014 | accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref> [[BBC America]] included the series in its first co-production deal with BBC Worldwide.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.televisual.com/news-detail/BBCW-Channels-and-BBC-America-strike-first-co-pro-deal_nid-3386.html | title=BBCW Channels and BBC America strike first co-pro deal | work=Televisual | date=17 October 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Considine, Pippa}}</ref> Lucy Pilkington is the [[executive producer]] for BBC Knowledge.<ref name="BBC" /><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.televisual.com/news-detail/360-to-make-10-part-fact-ent-series-for-BBC-Worldwide_nid-2827.html | title=360 to make 10-part fact ent series for BBC Worldwide | work=Televisual | date=17 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Considine, Pippa}}</ref>

